{"url":"https://community.fantasyflightgames.com/topic/70901-elrond-and-journey-to-rhosgobel/","title":"Elrond and Journey to Rhosgobel","comments":[{"commentUrl":"https://community.fantasyflightgames.com/topic/70901-elrond-and-journey-to-rhosgobel/?do=findComment&comment=692613","commentId":692613,"userName":"sangohan357","timestamp":1347501237,"content":" During the second quest step, the card says that you have to destroy every card which heal Wilyador.\n\nDoes Elrond effect count as a \"healing card\" ?! Do you have to destroy it ?"},{"commentUrl":"https://community.fantasyflightgames.com/topic/70901-elrond-and-journey-to-rhosgobel/?do=findComment&comment=692637","commentId":692637,"userName":"muemakan","timestamp":1347506834,"content":" Yes.                       "},{"commentUrl":"https://community.fantasyflightgames.com/topic/70901-elrond-and-journey-to-rhosgobel/?do=findComment&comment=693189","commentId":693189,"userName":"Golden_Nightingale","timestamp":1347566031,"content":"Be careful of even using a healing card with Elrond as your hero. He has a Response effect which takes place whenever a character is healed. AKA, it's not optional."},{"commentUrl":"https://community.fantasyflightgames.com/topic/70901-elrond-and-journey-to-rhosgobel/?do=findComment&comment=693214","commentId":693214,"userName":"Angus Lee","timestamp":1347568645,"content":"\"Response\" effects are optional; \"Forced\" effects are compulsory."}]}